com.cyc.query

Interface QueryResultSet

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<QueryAnswer>

    public interface QueryResultSet
extends Iterable<QueryAnswer>
    QueryResultSet defines an interface for easy access and manipulation of inference results. It tries to closely mimic the ResultSet class, but also provides an Iterable.iterator() method for QueryAnswer objects.

      • next

        boolean next()
        Moves the cursor forward one row from its current position. A QueryResultSetImpl cursor is initially positioned before the first row; the first call to the method next makes the first row the current row; the second call makes the second row the current row, and so on.
        Returns:
        true if the new current row is valid; false if there are no more rows

      • close

        void close()
        Releases this QueryResultSetImpl object's server side inference resources. Failure to close a result set may leave significant resources hanging around the server until the client CycAccess object is closed.

        Calling the method close on a InferenceResultSet object that is already closed is a no-op.

        String getString(int columnIndex)
        Returns, as a String, the value at the current row and at the column identified by columnIndex. Returns null if no value is set for the current row and given column.

      • getDate

        Date getDate(int columnIndex)
        Returns, as a java.sql.Date object, the value in the current row at the column identified by columnIndex position. Returns null if no value is set for the current row and given column. This method fails on dates that do not use #$YearFn (i.e. it will not work on skolemized dates, or other forms of dates that don't use the #$YearFn vocabulary).
        Parameters:
        columnIndex -
        Returns:
        the value at the current row and at the column identified by columnLabel as a Date object
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if columnLabel is not valid
        ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException - if the current cursor is not on a valid row
        ClassCastException - if the value is not convertible to a Date
